ughness of the film morphologies. The critical temperature at the transition can be identified either by the peak of the noise-reduced interface width (W *) or the peak of the noise-reduced roughness exponent (\u03b1*). The critical temperature and exponent (\u03bd) obtained here are consistent with those obtained from conventional methods. \u00a9 2013 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.", "prism:coverDate": "2013-12-15", "prism:aggregationType": "Journal", "prism:url": "https://api.elsevier.com/content/abstract/scopus_id/84885026849", "dc:creator": {"author": [{"preferred-name": {"ce:given-name": "M.", "ce:initials": "M.", "ce:surname": "Klawtanong", "ce:indexed-name": "Klawtanong M."}, "@seq": "1", "ce:initials": "M.", "@_fa": "true", "affiliation": {"@id": "60001884", "@href": "https://api.elsevier.com/content/affiliation/affiliation_id/60001884"}, "ce:surname": "Klawtanong", "@auid": "55845022500", "author-url": "https://api.elsevier.com/content/author/author_id/55845022500", "ce:indexed-name": "Klawtanong M."}]}, "link": [{"@_fa": "true", "@rel": "self", "@href": "https://api.elsevier.com/content/abstract/scopus_id/84885026849"}, {"@_fa": "true", "@rel": "scopus", "@href": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=84885026849&origin=inward"}, {"@_fa": "true", "@rel": "scopus-citedby", "@href": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/citedby.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=84885026849&origin=inward"}], "source-id": "29115", "pii": "S0378437113007164", "citedby-count": "0", "prism:volume": "392", "subtype": "ar", "dc:title": "Chiral symmetry breaking in FAXY model with roughness exponent method", "openaccess": "0", "prism:issn": "03784371", "prism:issueIdentifier": "24", "subtypeDescription": "Article", "prism:publicationName": "Physica A: Statistical Mechanics and its Applications", "prism:pageRange": "6307-6313", "prism:endingPage": "6313", "openaccessFlag": "false", "prism:doi": "10.1016/j.physa.2013.08.005", "prism:startingPage": "6307", "dc:identifie